  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The diagnosis of pneumonia is challenging in Intensive Care Unit. The auto-fluorescence of
      white corpuscles is altered during pneumonia. In presence of bacterial growth on lung
      samples, the measure of autofluorescence of white corpuscles could help the clinicians to
      discriminate bacterial colonization from acute infection.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
